&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Agenda&lt;/strong&gt;: The Oct. 21, System of Care Advisory Council (SOCAC) meeting will include a Local SOC Spotlight presentation from the Columbia Gorge System of Care. The Council will focus on reviewing the SOCAC Strategic Plan, with time dedicated to reflecting on each goal area and discussing progress toward meeting the Council&rsquo;s legislative mandate to create a statewide plan for the children&rsquo;s behavioral health system.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Following the main review, Council members and participants will take part in small group discussions to review the draft Implementation Plan, identify priorities, and provide feedback to strengthen statewide coordination and accountability.&amp;nbsp; Public comment will be heard at approximately 2:30 p.m.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.oregon.gov/oha/HSD/BH-Child-Family/Pages/SOCAC.aspx" style="text-size-adjust: 100%; color: rgb(6, 66, 118);"&gt;The full agenda can be found here&lt;/a&gt;&lt;u&gt;.&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

