&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Oregon State Police&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Oregon State Police (OSP) is a multidisciplinary organization charged with protecting the people, wildlife, and natural resources in Oregon. OSP enforces traffic laws on the state&rsquo;s roadways, investigates and solves crime, conducts postmortem examinations and forensic analysis, and provides background checks, and law enforcement data. The agency regulates gaming and enforces fish, wildlife, and natural resource laws. OSP is comprised of more than 1,400 staff members &ndash; including troopers, investigators, and professional staff &ndash; who provide a full range of policing and public safety services to Oregon and to other law enforcement agencies throughout the state.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

