&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Background:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;The Oregon Emergency Medical Services Advisory Board was established under the 2024 EMS Modernization Act (&lt;a href="https://olis.oregonlegislature.gov/liz/2024R1/Downloads/MeasureDocument/HB4081" style="text-size-adjust: 100%; color: rgb(6, 66, 118);"&gt;HB 4081 | 2024&lt;/a&gt;,&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://www.oregonlegislature.gov/bills_laws/lawsstatutes/2024orLaw0032.pdf" style="text-size-adjust: 100%; color: rgb(6, 66, 118);"&gt;OL Ch 32&lt;/a&gt;) to oversee systems of emergency medical care statewide. The Board comprises 19 members, chaired by the State EMS Medical Director. The Emergency Medical Services Advisory Board advises Oregon Health Authority&rsquo;s Emergency Medical Services Program on evidence-based practices and standards for defined patient types, emergency medical services workforce needs, and coordination of care between health care specialties.&lt;/p&gt;

