&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Background&lt;/strong&gt;: Established by Ballot Measure 109 (2020), the&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://www.oregon.gov/oha/ph/preventionwellness/pages/psilocybin-advisory-board-meetings.aspx" style="text-size-adjust: 100%; color: rgb(6, 66, 118);"&gt;Oregon Psilocybin Advisory Board&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;makes recommendations to Oregon Health Authority (OHA) on available scientific studies and research on the safety and efficacy of psilocybin in treating mental health conditions. The Board makes recommendations on the requirements, specifications and guidelines for providing psilocybin services in Oregon.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Board will also develop a long-term strategic plan for ensuring psilocybin services become and remain a safe, accessible and affordable therapeutic option for all persons 21 and older in this state for whom psilocybin may be appropriate. It also will monitor and study federal laws, regulations and policies regarding psilocybin.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;# # #&lt;/p&gt;

