&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:calibri,calibri_embeddedfont,calibri_msfontservice,sans-serif; font-size:12pt"&gt;The affordable housing projects, approved by the &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a class="Hyperlink SCXW163655267 BCX8" href="https://www.oregon.gov/ohcs/hsc/Pages/index.aspx" rel="noreferrer noopener" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; user-select: text; -webkit-user-drag: none; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; text-decoration-line: none;" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 255); font-family:calibri,calibri_embeddedfont,calibri_msfontservice,sans-serif; font-size:12pt"&gt;Oregon Housing Stability Council&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:calibri,calibri_embeddedfont,calibri_msfontservice,sans-serif; font-size:12pt"&gt; (HSC), span both urban centers and rural communities and represent an investment of more than $100 million in affordable housing this month.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class="OutlineElement Ltr SCXW163655267 BCX8" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; user-select: text; -webkit-user-drag: none; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; overflow: visible; cursor: text; clear: both; position: relative; direction: ltr; font-family: &amp;quot;Segoe UI&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;Segoe UI Web&amp;quot;, Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:calibri,calibri_embeddedfont,calibri_msfontservice,sans-serif; font-size:12pt"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class="OutlineElement Ltr SCXW163655267 BCX8" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; user-select: text; -webkit-user-drag: none; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; overflow: visible; cursor: text; clear: both; position: relative; direction: ltr; font-family: &amp;quot;Segoe UI&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;Segoe UI Web&amp;quot;, Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:calibri,calibri_embeddedfont,calibri_msfontservice,sans-serif; font-size:12pt"&gt;&ldquo;This is shared progress with housing partners across the state. Every month, we move towards a future where every Oregonian has a safe, stable, and affordable place to call home,&rdquo; said Mary Farrell, member of the HSC. &ldquo;These homes represent hope, opportunity, and a more equitable Oregon.&rdquo;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:calibri,calibri_embeddedfont,calibri_msfontservice,sans-serif; font-size:12pt"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

